data.title: BHDD: Primordial black hole binaries code
data.name: BlackHolesDarkDress
data.description: Code for studying primordial black hole (PBH) binaries, clothed in dark matter (DM) halos, associated with the paper "Black Holes' Dark Dress: On the merger rate of a subdominant population of primordial black holes".

evidence: README mentions binaries/installers: "* `notebooks/` - Contains jupyter notebooks for performing the main calculations in the paper associated with the PDFs of binary system, as well as calculating the merger rates and LIGO limits."

"Code for studying primordial black hole (PBH) binaries, clothed in dark matter (DM) halos, associated with the paper... We use N-body simulations... to follow the evolution of PBH binaries formed in the early Universe."
"The main calculations are given in `notebooks/MergerRate.ipynb` and `notebooks/LIGO_limits.ipynb`."
